author: marvin
msg: Merge StringHelper3.c into StringHelper.c, remove Unicode license.
This file StringHelper3.c, which contains only a single function
StrHelp_is_whitespace(), is currently listed under the Unicode Consortium's
license.  I wrote that file myself, but erring on the side of paranoia, I
credited the Unicode Consortium for having defined the character class.  I now
believe that this was incorrect, and I am not aware of any other projects
that have done likewise.  StrHelp_is_whitespace() implements a function using
the Unicode standard; it is not a modified redistribution of Unicode data
